main event: A fast-moving object the size of a jet wing tank was observed emitting a brilliant flame over Munich, Germany on February 21, 1960.
interesting points: The object was observed for 3-5 seconds by two civilian witnesses on the ground.
The object was light in color and had a tail.
It was moving at a high rate of speed from southeast to northwest.
Satellite, astronomical, radar, and natural phenomena were ruled out as possible explanations.
The reliability of the witnesses was considered to be good.
sighted object: a fast-moving object the size of a jet wing tank emitting a brilliant flame
